# Vercel auto-deploy (Yaavs-Web)

When you finish user-requested changes to this website, deploy them unless the user explicitly says not to.

## End-of-task workflow

1. Stage and commit only the files you changed (concise message focused on why).
2. Push to `origin/main`.
3. Deploy production from the repo root:
   ```bash
   npx vercel --prod --yes
   ```
   Or: `./scripts/deploy-vercel.sh`
4. Tell the user the live URL: https://yaavs-web.vercel.app

## Notes

- The project is linked via `.vercel/project.json` (`yaavs-web`).
- Bump CSS/JS cache-bust query params in HTML when those assets change.
- Skip commit/push/deploy only when the user asks for local-only or draft work.
